Worked example 1: verify a solution
Show that y = 2e^{3x} solves dy/dx = 3y.
Step 1: Differentiate the candidate.
y = 2e^{3x}
y' = 6e^{3x}
Step 2: Compute the right-hand side 3y.
3y = 3(2e^{3x}) = 6e^{3x}
Step 3: Compare.
y' = 6e^{3x} and 3y = 6e^{3x}
They match, so the candidate is a solution.

